cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.DL. 

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based framework for slide quality assessment, which involves image classification, semantic analysis, and information visualization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of histograms and text summaries, which suggests that it may belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning models and the focus on performance evaluation indicate that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DL (Deep Learning).
